neither very con&s;iderable, nor very cer|tain;
what effects may it not be expected
to produce, when it re&s;ts upon an object
&s;o &s;plendid, as a life of immortal felicity?
Were this hope entertained -with that full
per&s;ua&s;ion which Chri&s;tian faith demands,
it would, in truth, not merely alleviate,
