that, &s;ome particular ca&s;es excepted, it is
no other than the abu&s;e of it.</P>
<P>But, though entire retreat would lay us
a&s;ide from the part for which Providence
chiefly intended us, it is certain, that
without occa&s;ional retreat, we mu&s;t act
<PB N="236" REF="245">
that part very ill. There will be neither
