<P>II. To recommend this devout &s;pirit
to your imitation. I begin with ob&s;erv|ing,
that it is of the unmo&s;t con&s;equence
to guard again&s;t extremes of every kind
in religion. We mu&s;t beware, le&s;t, by
&s;eeking to avoid one rock, we &s;plit upon
