than compen&s;ated by &s;ucceeding pain;
Whether, if not from every particular
in&s;tance, yet from every habit, at lea&s;t,
of unlawful gratification, there did not
&s;pring &s;ome thorn to wound you, there
did not ari&s;e &s;ome con&s;equence to make
you repent of it in the i&s;&s;ue? <HI>How long
<PB N="331" REF="340">
then, ye &s;imple ones! will $word$ &s;implicity?</HI>
